# Testing strategy (clean architecture)

Pyramid (~50–60% unit, ~25–30% integration, ~10–15% e2e) is a **maturity baremo**, not a sprint quota. Physical layout and naming live under `test/` — see `test/README.md` and `docs/architecture/testing-strategy.md`.

## Where to put tests

| Layer | Path | Naming |
|-------|------|--------|
| Domain | `test/domain/**` | `*.spec.ts` |
| Use case | `test/application/**` | `*.integration.spec.ts` |
| Adapter | `test/contracts/**` | `*.contract.spec.ts` |
| Journey | `test/e2e/journeys/**` | Playwright `*.spec.ts` |
| Shared builders | `test/support/{fixtures,doubles}` | reusable across non-e2e |
| E2E builders | `test/e2e/{fixtures,doubles,support}` | Playwright-only |

Do **not** add new `*.spec.ts` next to production files under `src/`.

## Do

- Import production code with `@/` and shared test helpers with `@test/` (maps to `test/`).
- Prefer fixing behavior with the **lowest** useful layer (domain unit before e2e).
- Fake ports in application tests; no real network/device storage.
- When touching an adapter, add/update a contract in `test/contracts` (~100% of the public surface touched).
- Put ready data in `fixtures/`, route/API fakes in `doubles/`.
- Climb toward the baremo incrementally — add missing layers; do not delete useful domain units to “fix” percentages.

## Do not

- Do not call a single pure-function spec an integration test.
- Do not mock the domain under test in its own unit test.
- Do not add trivial UI render snapshots without a business/contract assertion.
- Do not require e2e for every component change.
- Do not skip adapter contract tests without an explicit PR note (e.g. pure rename).

## PR checklist (when code changes)

- [ ] Domain touched → unit covers the rule (+ edge/warning if relevant)
- [ ] Use case touched → integration with fakes
- [ ] Adapter touched → contract for the public API changed
- [ ] Critical journey touched → e2e considered / updated if needed

## Commands

- `pnpm run test:unit` — domain + application + contracts
- `pnpm run test:e2e` — Playwright under `test/e2e`
- `pnpm run test:ci` — full quality gate
